+# Chroma Modular Architecture
+
+This project follows a modular architecture to improve maintainability, scalability, and separation of concerns. The codebase is organized into distinct modules based on functionality.
+
+## Python Components
+
+- `chromadb/core/` - Core business logic and entities
+- `chromadb/api/` - API interfaces and implementations
+- `chromadb/db/` - Database interfaces and implementations
+- `chromadb/server/` - Server components
+- `chromadb/cli/` - Command-line interface
+- `chromadb/client/` - Client-side code for connecting to server
+- `chromadb/segment/` - Segment management
+- `chromadb/utils/` - General utilities
+- `chromadb/config/` - Configuration management
+- `chromadb/telemetry/` - Telemetry and monitoring
+- `chromadb/auth/` - Authentication and authorization
+
+## Rust Components
+
+- `rust/worker/src/core/` - Core business logic and entities
+- `rust/worker/src/database/` - Database interfaces and implementations
+- `rust/worker/src/segment/` - Segment management
+- `rust/worker/src/server/` - HTTP server components
+- `rust/worker/src/config/` - Configuration management
+- `rust/worker/src/utils/` - General utilities
+
+## Go Components
+
+- `go/pkg/core/` - Core business logic and entities
+- `go/pkg/database/` - Database interfaces and implementations
+- `go/pkg/segment/` - Segment management
+- `go/pkg/server/` - HTTP server components
+- `go/pkg/config/` - Configuration management
+- `go/pkg/client/` - Client-side code for connecting to server
+- `go/pkg/utils/` - General utilities
+
+## Benefits of Modular Architecture
+
+1. **Separation of Concerns**: Each module has a specific responsibility
+2. **Maintainability**: Easier to understand, modify, and debug
+3. **Testability**: Modules can be tested independently
+4. **Scalability**: Easier to extend functionality
+5. **Reusability**: Components can be reused across different parts of the system
